# Build context for the colibri Docker images.
#
# The Dockerfile lives at docker/Dockerfile, but its build CONTEXT is the
# repo root (so the COPY c/ /opt/colibri/c/ instruction resolves). Without
# this file, `docker build` would walk the entire working tree and tarball
# ~370 GB worth of safetensors shards, the .git directory, the web/node_modules,
# the desktop/target, etc. — every one of which is dead weight at build time.
#
# Strategy: deny everything, then allow exactly what the Dockerfiles need.
#   - c/                     — the engine source, Makefile, and Python CLI
#   - docker/                — healthcheck.py and (for the .cuda image) any
#                              cross-stage artifacts we copy in
#
# Everything else (models, .git, web/node_modules, desktop/target, docs
# PDF renders, *.pyc, .DS_Store) is excluded by the leading `*` rule.

# Deny everything
*
# Allow the engine directory and everything in it
!c/
!c/**
# Allow the docker directory itself (needed if a future stage COPYs from it)
!docker/
!docker/**
